  "Anthony Edwards": "Edwards recently missed six consecutive games due to right knee pain and may be held out of the front end of this back-to-back set. If the star guard is ruled out, Bones Hyland, Mike Conley and Terrence Shannon would be candidates to see increased playing time. Edwards returned from the extended absence in Monday's blowout win over Dallas, posting 17 points (7-13 FG, 2-3 3Pt, 1-1 FT), four assists and two rebounds across 23 minutes.",
